[[Introduction_to_Philosophy|Introduction to Philosophy]] > [[Introduction_to_Philosophy/Logic|Logic]] > Formal Logic

Logicians describe various formal systems of logic which are intended to match a precise but limited range of reasoning.  Each such system defines a formal language.  A scope of such a system&mdash;and the corresponding expressability of its formal language&mdash;matches the range of reasoning it is supposed to describe.

